of ^ti~ in ^siati~ preceding; this explains the omission of ^a~
before it.  A few MSS. read ^A te.~  |Che il ventre~, &c.: `which
thus raises thy belly like a hedge in front of thine eyes,' i.e.
causes it to obstruct thy sight.
